pnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Animal Training: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 training animals for specific tasks. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Arcane Lore:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  knowledge of occult things \endash  otherworldly stories, legends, etc. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Area Knowledge: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 knowledge of a given area.  The larger the area, the more shallow the knowledge. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Armorer:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  making, altering, and repairing armor. [Terrible] (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Artist:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  creating aesthetically pleasing art in a given medium.  Each medium is a separate skill. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Astrology: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 this is either simple astronomy or an actual potent forecasting and divination tool \endash  ask the GM. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Balance:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  keeping one\rquote s equilibrium in awkward physical situations, such as tightrope walking, beam walking, crossing a stream on a log, etc. (Athletic)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Barroom Savvy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  like Urban Survival, but very specific to barrooms. (Social, Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Barter/Haggle:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  raising or reducing prices, depending on whether you\rquote re selling or buying.  Opposed by the other person\rquote s Barter/Haggle skill. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Basketry: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 making baskets and other woven products from bark, grasses, and other plant materials.  Includes a knowledge of materials, market prices, etc. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bluff: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 misleading people into thinking you will perform an action you have no intention of performing.  Opposed by Reasoning. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Boating: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 small boat handling. (Athletic, Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bookkeeping:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  knowledge of accounting practices \endash  requires Literacy and some math ability. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Botany: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 broad knowledge of plants \endash  their habitats, growing needs, uses, dangers, etc.  See Herb Lore, Farming, Basketry, Poisons, etc., for more specific skills. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bow: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 using and caring for a bow and arrows, either longbow or short bow. [Terrible] (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bowyer/Fletcher:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  making bows and arrows, including harvesting the appropriate material. [Terrible] (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Brawling:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  fighting without weapons. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Camaraderie:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  being entertaining in social settings, such as at a bar, at a party, around a campfire, etc., which can gain someone\rquote s confidence and approval. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Camouflage: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 blending in with your surroundings so you don\rquote t stand out. Primarily used in natural settings \endash  use Disguise in urban settings. (However, a case could be made for using Camouflage skill to hide in an alley, for example.) (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Camping:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  similar to Survival, but requires some tools, such as blankets, pots, an axe, a tent, etc.  In return, it allows greater comfort and quality of life in the wild. (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Carpentry: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 working with wood, to make anything from houses to furniture to cabinets. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Climbing: c}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 limbing, either natural formations such as cliffs and trees, or man-made ones such as stone, brick, etc., (but not sheer) walls. (Athletic, Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Club/Mace:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  using a club or mace as a combat weapon. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Con: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 making people believe in some plan or product you are pushing. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Cooking: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 preparing tasty and nourishing food. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Counseling/Priest: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 comforting the afflicted, restoring good emotional health, helping people through grief, etc. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Courtesan:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  professional pleasure giving. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Crossbow: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 using a crossbow effectively in combat. [Mediocre] (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Dancing: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 dancing aesthetically. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Detect Lies:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  telling when someone is lying.  Opposed by Lies/Pretense. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Detect Traps:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  determining if a given area has a trap of some sort set, and what type. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Diplomacy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  not a separate skill \endash  see Parley/Negotiate\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Disarm Traps: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 deactivating a trap without harm.  This may or may not cause noise, however\u8230\'c9.(Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Disguise: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 passing for someone else under visual inspection.  There is a penalty for serious inspection, of course.  Opposed by Reasoning, though no roll is needed if the observer has no reason to be suspicious. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Engineer: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 designing and making tools, structures, sewer systems, etc. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Equestrian Acrobatics: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 performing acrobatic mounts, dismounts, trick riding, etc.  This skill cannot be higher than your Riding skill. (Athletic)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Etiquette: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 knowledge of good manners in any society, and the ability to carry them out.  Not as specific as Savoir-Faire, but gives a broader base for knowledge. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Evaluate Goods: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 a general skill to assess the value of something.  It won\rquote t be as accurate as a specific Professional skill (for example, a Potter will be a better judge of Pottery than someone with this skill), but as a broad skill allows a good general knowledge. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Falconry: t}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 raining and controlling a raptor for sport and hunting. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Farming:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  raising crops and/or livestock, and everything associated with that: soil preparation, planting, weeding, tending, harvest, drying, storage, markets, etc. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Fast-draw: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 readying a weapon for combat use effectively instantly. A different skill for each weapon, and some weapons cannot be fast-drawn. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Fast-talk:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  convincing someone of something, which, upon reflection, they may realize isn\rquote t true. Fast-talk doesn\rquote t create lasting belief \endash  see the Con skill for that.  Opposed by Reasoning. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Find Hidden:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  locating concealed doors, compartments, catches, etc. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 First aid:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  administering emergency medical treatment knowledgeably. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Fishing:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  catching fish for food, sale, barter, or sport. (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Flail: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 using a flail as a weapon. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Flatter: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 making people like you by complimenting them to the point they begin to trust your judgement. Opposed by Willpower. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Flirt/Vamp:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  arousing sexual interest in an appropriate subject, for whatever reason. Opposed by Willpower. (Social)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Forgery:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  making fake documents and/or signatures that look authentic. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Gambling:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  gaming for money. Note that some gambling includes games of skill, and others games of chance \endash  this skill helps largely with the former, and knowledge of the latter, including a good estimate of the odds. Also the ability to cheat at games, and spot cheaters. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Geography:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  broader than Area Knowledge, Geography is the knowledge of general topography, terrain nature, biomes, etc. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs