d by Perception. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Tailor: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 turning cloth into clothes, as well as mending clothing. Can also make other items out of cloth, such as tents. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Teaching: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 imparting knowledge or skills to others. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Team Acrobatics:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  working with others trained in this skill to perform acrobatic maneuvers such as stacking, vaulting, trapeze work, etc. (Athletic)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Teamster: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 handling an animal or team of animals pulling a wagon, carriage, coach, etc. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Thaumatology:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  the knowledge of magic spells, results, abilities, etc. Does not require any Magical Ability, nor is it required to perform magic. [No Default] (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Theater: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 the skills and knowledge associated with the theater: acting, directing, management of props, sets, the house, the stage, etc. Not the same as pretending to be someone else offstage \endash  see Lie/Pretense for that skill. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Theology/Myths/Rituals: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 knowledge of a specific religion\rquote s beliefs, dogma, and rituals. It may also be Comparative Theology, in which case the knowledge is broader \endash  covers more than one religion \endash  but shallower. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Throwing:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  throwing things accurately, but not specifically optimized to do damage. That is, it\rquote s not a combat skill, though it could be used as one, with \endash 1 to damage-dealing ability. (Athletic)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Tracking: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 following animals or sentient beings in terrain where they might leave traces. Of limited use in urban areas, it is more a nature skill. (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Trail Blazing:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  finding an optimum route through wilderness, and marking your trail, either obviously or subtly. (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Two-handed Axe: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 using any two-handed axe designed as a weapon. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Two-handed Sword:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  using any two-handed sword as a weapon. (Combat)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Urban Survival:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  the skill of the urban poor: where to find free or cheap food, shelter and clothing; what parts of the city to avoid, who not to offend, etc. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Ventriloquism:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  \ldblquote throwing your voice\rdblquote  so as to make it sound as if it comes from somewhere else.  Also disguising your voice. (Covert)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Veterinarian: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 diagnosing and treating animal injuries and diseases. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Weather Sense: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 predicting the weather for the near future. (Knowledge)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Weaving: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 spinning yarn from wool or plants, then making cloth from yarn. (Professional)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Whittling: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 carving wood into useful or aesthetic shapes. (Athletic)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Woods Lore:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  knowledge of woodland animals, plants, cycles, etc. (Scouting)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Zoology: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 knowledge of animal behavior, habits, diets, capabilities, etc. (Knowledge)\par \par }\pard \sb240\sa60\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\fs26\kerning1 Attributes\par }\pard \sa120\sl240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 There are six attributes in Fantasy Fudge. The GM may customize this list as she wishes \endash  changing the attributes included, adding or deleting them at will.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Reasoning:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  Thinking ability; puzzle-solving; intelligence; mental acuity.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Perception:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  Awareness of the environment; raw ability to notice things.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Willpower: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Strength of will; psychic stamina; determination; guts.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Strength:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  Physical strength; lifting/ carrying capacity; ability to deal damage.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Agility: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Physical dexterity; adroitness; native talent for physical skills.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Health:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  Fitness; resistance to disease and injury; physical stamina.\par \par }{\b\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Allocating Attributes\par }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 All attributes start at Fair.  Each character may take two free attribute levels, either raising one attribute two levels, or two attributes one level each.  (The GM may allow more or fewer free attribute levels \endash  see Campaign Power Levels in the online version of Five-point Fudge.)\par In addition, players may trade levels \endash  that is, lower an attribute to Mediocre in order to raise one other attribute one level, and so on.  Also, subject to GM approval, a character may raise an attribute by taking an additional Fault, or by foregoing one of the two free Gifts.\par Conversely, a player may forego one of his free two attribute levels in order to take an extra Gift \endash  again, subject to GM approval.\par Attributes are not linked to skills in this game.  The player is encouraged to choose attribute levels which make sense, given his skill list. For example, three or more points spent between Combat, Scouting and Athletic skills means that the character would logically be above average in Strength, Agility, and/or Health. If the player decides not to raise at least one of these attributes above Fair, he should have a good story as to why they are abnormally low.\par \par }{\b\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Using Attributes\par }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Attributes are used for three things in the game:\par \bullet  As very broad skills. There will be times in which no particular skill listed in the rules is appropriate for the task the character is attempting. In these cases, the GM will choose the closest attribute and have the player roll versus the attribute.\par \bullet  In certain opposed actions, such as attempting to sneak by a guard (Move Quietly skill vs. Perception attribute) or a swindle attempt (Con skill vs. Reasoning attribute) or an attempt to strangle someone (Strength attribute vs. Health attribute). The GM will think of other cases readily.\par \bullet  As a broad handle on who the character is. A high Reasoning, low Strength character has a different flavor from the opposite attribute levels.\par \par }\pard \sb240\sa60\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\fs26\kerning1 Gifts\par }\pard \sa120\sl240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Each character may have two Gifts from the following list, or other GM-approved Gift. In addition, for each Fault chosen beyond the first two, the character may have an additional Gift. The GM may limit the number Gifts available from this method, as things can get a little out of hand\u8230\'c9. You may also gain a Gift, with GM approval, by foregoing one of your free attribute levels.\par Certain Gifts, marked with an asterisk (*), may be lost if abused. Contacts, Favors Due, and Patron depend on the goodwill of others, and it\rquote s possible to push them too far or too frequently. Good Reputation can be eroded by inappropriate behavior, and Rank can be lost if you break the rules of the organization granting the rank.\par \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Ambidexterity: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you can use either hand equally well.  Great for those times when you\rquote re wounded in an arm\u8230\'c9.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Attractive:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re good looking \endash  either handsome, beautiful, pretty, or whatever you wish. (Warning: the more attractive you are, the more power you have over susceptible people, true, but the more likely you are to be abducted, etc.)\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Beautiful speaking voice:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  +1 to NPC reactions.  Also works for a singing voice if you take a Musical skill.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Charisma:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  people tend to like you, believe you, and are willing to follow your lead.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Common Sense:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  when you are about to do something incredibly stupid that will harm yourself or the party, the GM will warn you.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Contacts *: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you know some influential or knowledgeable people who can supply you with information.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Danger Sense:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  the GM will make a Situational roll \endash  on a Good or better result, you\rquote ll be warned of some imminent danger.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Divine Favor:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  the ability to cast Clerical Magic \endash  see Clerical Magic, below.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Empathy with Animals:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  animals trust you and domesticated ones tend to obey you. Cruelty to animals nullifies this Gift.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Empathy with Sentient Beings: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 see Innate Magical Ability: Second Sight, below.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Familiar: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 only available to characters with the Magical Talent Gift. You have a magical familiar, which may talk, aid you in spell-casting and other tasks. This is an NPC played by the GM.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Favors due *:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  some people owe you favors, which you may collect. Each favor you collect must be approved by the GM.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Focused:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you are at +1 to any lengthy task, but don\rquote t notice things outside this task, such as that brigand about to skewer you\u8230\'c9.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Good Memory:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you have an unusually good memory.  The player may take notes during the game and act as if the character remembered them.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Good Reputation *:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re well known as a hero, healer, leader, fighter for justice, etc.\par High Status: you are of the gentry or religious class \endash  or nobility if you take this Gift twice.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Intuition: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you have a feeling about what option to take when confronted with a choice.  The GM will make a Situational roll in secret.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Lucky:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  once per hour (real time), you may reroll a bad dice roll, and choose the better of the two rolls.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Magic Resistance: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you are resistant to direct magic: +3 to Willpower in any Opposed rolls versus magic.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Magical Talent (specify type):}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  the ability to perform magical feats. There are three different types of Magical Talent: Innate Magic, Hedge Magic, and Scholarly Magic. You may take multiple levels of the same type of Magic Talent.  See Magic, below, for details.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Never forgets a ____: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 fill in the blank with name, face, or whatever the GM will allow.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Never Gets Lost:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you always know which way is North, and can retrace your route with a little effort.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Night Vision: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you see well in dim light, but not in absolute darkness, of course.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Pain Tolerance: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 ignore wound penalties at Hurt, and you are only at \endash 1 at Very Hurt.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Patron *: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 someone in power likes you. This can be simply a letter of recommendation, or it can be a favor granted.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Perfect Timing:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  if someone says to open the gate in five minutes, you\rquote ll do it within two seconds of that time. Also valuable in performing.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Peripheral Vision:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you can see further to the sides than most people \endash  less easily attacked from the side or rear.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Quick Reflexes: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 not easily surprised by any physical attack, and you adjust quickly to shifting footing.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Rank *:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you have the right to command others in an organized body of soldiers or police.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Rapid Healing: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you heal twice as fast from wounds \endash  but not magically fast.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Resistant to Poison:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  poison has only half effect on you. \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Tough Hide:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  subtract 1 from each amount of damage you take. \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Veteran: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you\rquote re experienced \endash  add one level to each of three skills that are currently at Fair or Mediocre.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Wealthy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you start with more money than the average starting character. This can be in cash and/or equipment.\par \par }\pard \sb240\sa60\nowidctlpar\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\b\fs26\kerning1 Faults\par }\pard \sa120\sl240\slmult0\nowidctlpar\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Each character must start with two Faults from the following list, or other GM-approved Fault. In addition, each Fault chosen beyond the mandatory two allows the player to choose an additional Gift for his character, or raise an attribute one level, subject to GM approval.\par \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Absent-Minded: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 your attention tends to wander if bored.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Annoying Voice: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you sound terrible.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Appearance:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  your appearance is off-putting in some way, whether ugly or unkempt.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bad Back: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you are limited in what you can lift.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Bad Eyesight: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you don\rquote t see very well \endash  pick one: poor distance or up-close vision.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Blunt and Tactless:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you have no social skills in dealing with sensitive people.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Code of Honor: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 your actions are constrained by your personal behavior code.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Color Blindness:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you confuse lots of colors.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Combat Paralysis:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you need a Good or better Health roll in order to act in a dangerous situation. \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Compulsive Carousing: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you are at \endash 3 Willpower to resist a good time.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Compulsive Gambling: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 your are at \endash 3 Willpower to resist a gambling game.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Compulsive Generosity:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you are at \endash 3 Willpower to resist giving things away to those perceived to be needier than you.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Compulsive Lying: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you are at \endash 3 Willpower to avoid lying just for fun.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Coward:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you take very good care of yourself.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Curious:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you are at \endash 3 Willpower to resist exploring something new or unusual.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Delusions: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 the world doesn\rquote t work the way you think it does, in some important way.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Dependent:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re responsible for someone unable to care for themselves adequately.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Duty: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you must perform active duty a certain amount of time.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Dwarfism:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you are very short for your race.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Easily Distractible:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  did you say something?\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Easy to Read:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you give away your thoughts and feelings to any who care to observe you.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Enemy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  there is someone who wants to kill, imprison, or otherwise trouble you.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Fanatic Patriot:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  your country, right or wrong.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Frightens Animals:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you have an aura that animals find terrifying.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Garrulous: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you won\rquote t shut up.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Getting old:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  and all that implies.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Glutton:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re hungry.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Goes Berserk if Wounded:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re a danger to your friends, even.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Greedy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you want more.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Grouchy:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you\rquote re usually irritated and try to spread the mood.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Gullible:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  -3 to Reasoning to believe an unknown \ldblquote fact.\rdblquote \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Hard of Hearing:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  what?\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Honesty:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you hate to break a law. See Truthfulness for not liking to lie.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Humanitarian: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you help the needy for no pay.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Idealist: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you\rquote re not grounded in reality.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Impulsive:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you act before thinking.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Intolerant: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you hate a certain type of person.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Jealous of Anyone Getting More Attention: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you have to be the star.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Lame: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you limp, which can affect speed and agility.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Lazy: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you work hard at avoiding work.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Lechery: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you\rquote re overly fond of the appropriate sex.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Loyal to Companions:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you won\rquote t abandon, cheat, hide treasure from, etc., the party members. This one may be mandatory.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Magic Susceptibility:}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1  you are at \endash 3 Willpower to oppose hostile magic.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Melancholy: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 life is so sad. \par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 Miserliness: }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerning1 you hate to let it go.\par }{\i\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-1\kerni